        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When doing an authorization with Zend_OpenId_Consumer the realm gets mangled due to the use of dirname() in $this->_checkId() if I do not explicitly define a root when calling $consumer->login('', 'return_to', 'root').  I don't entirely know why dirname() is being called on line 729\n\n        if (empty($root)) {\n            $root = dirname(Zend_OpenId::selfUrl());\n        }\n\nbut when I remove the dirname(), the consumer auto-discovers the URL just fine and I'm able to validate the login request.  Otherwise I get a BAD_REQUEST response back from the OpenId provider.\n\nThis is being done with an MVC-based test application"
        },
