        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19009",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, but I'm not able to reproduce the issue.\nThe demo MVC application \"demo\/Zend\/OpenId\/mvc_auth\" works fine.\nThe bug is probably already fixed some time ago (svn diff -r 6835:7023 library\/Zend\/OpenId.php).\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-12T11:34:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-12T11:34:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19012",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kschroeder",
                        "name": "kschroeder",
                        "displayName": "Kevin Schroeder",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In the MVC example it uses Zend_Auth_Adapter_OpenId whereas I had used the code from the manual:\n\n[code]\n$status = \"\";\nif (isset($_POST['openid_action']) &&\n    $_POST['openid_action'] == \"login\" &&\n    !empty($_POST['openid_identifier'])) {\n\n    $consumer = new Zend_OpenId_Consumer();\n    if (!$consumer->login($_POST['openid_identifier'])) {\n        $status = \"OpenID login failed.<br>\";\n    }\n} else if (isset($_GET['openid_mode'])) {\n    if ($_GET['openid_mode'] == \"id_res\") {\n        $consumer = new Zend_OpenId_Consumer();\n        if ($consumer->verify($_GET, $id)) {\n            $status = \"VALID $id\";\n        } else {\n            $status = \"INVALID $id\";\n        }\n    } else if ($_GET['openid_mode'] == \"cancel\") {\n        $status = \"CANCELED\";\n    }\n}\n\n[\/code]\n\nIs Zend_Auth_Adapter_OpenId the only method for using it in MVC applications?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kschroeder",
                        "name": "kschroeder",
                        "displayName": "Kevin Schroeder",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-12T12:31:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-12T12:31:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19141",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Of course Zend_Auth_Adapter_OpenId is not the only case, it just simpler.\n\nCould you please attach the complete MVC example?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-15T02:04:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-15T02:04:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19149",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kschroeder",
                        "name": "kschroeder",
                        "displayName": "Kevin Schroeder",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "IndexController.php\n\nclass IndexController extends Zend_Controller_Action \n{\n    public function indexAction() \n    {\n\t\t\t    $status = \"\";\n\t\t\tif (isset($_POST['openid_action']) &&\n\t\t\t    $_POST['openid_action'] == \"login\" &&\n\t\t\t    !empty($_POST['openid_identifier'])) {\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t    $consumer = new Zend_OpenId_Consumer();\n\t\t\t    if (!$consumer->login($_POST['openid_identifier'])) {\n\t\t\t        $status = \"OpenID login failed.<br>\";\n\t\t\t    }\n\t\t\t} else if (isset($_GET['openid_mode'])) {\n\t\t\t    if ($_GET['openid_mode'] == \"id_res\") {\n\t\t\t        $consumer = new Zend_OpenId_Consumer();\n\t\t\t        if ($consumer->verify($_GET, $id)) {\n\t\t\t            $status = \"VALID $id\";\n\t\t\t        } else {\n\t\t\t            $status = \"INVALID $id\";\n\t\t\t        }\n\t\t\t    } else if ($_GET['openid_mode'] == \"cancel\") {\n\t\t\t        $status = \"CANCELED\";\n\t\t\t    }\n\t\t\t}\n    }\n}\n\nviews\/scripts\/index\/index.phtml\n\n<html><body>\n<form method=\"post\"><fieldset>\n<legend>OpenID Login<\/legend>\n<input type=\"text\" name=\"openid_identifier\" value=\"\">\n<input type=\"submit\" name=\"openid_action\" value=\"login\">\n<input type=\"submit\" name=\"openid_action\" value=\"logout\">\n<\/fieldset><\/form><\/body><\/html>\n\nMy OpenID provider is pip.verisignlabs.com.  My test URL is http:\/\/test.corp.mirageworks.com\/.  That domain name should be accessible from the public web if you want to test it out directly with your own ID.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kschroeder",
                        "name": "kschroeder",
                        "displayName": "Kevin Schroeder",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-15T07:34:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-15T07:34:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19152",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "At first you example says nothing in case of success. I've modified it a bit. In the controller I substituted $status with $this->view->status, and in the view I added <?php echo $this->staus; ?>\nThen I tested the example with myopenid.com and pip.verisignlabs.com and both worked fine.\n\nI assume the bug was already fixed in SVN and you use latest release or old snapshot.\n\nThank you anyway. :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-15T08:32:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-15T08:32:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19154",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kschroeder",
                        "name": "kschroeder",
                        "displayName": "Kevin Schroeder",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm still getting the error.  I checked out the latest revision from SVN, did a symbolic link to it so it replaced the other version.  The URL I am forwarded to is\n\nhttp:\/\/pip.verisignlabs.com\/server?openid.ns=http%3A%2F%2Fspecs.openid.net%2Fauth%2F2.0&openid.mode=checkid_setup&openid.identity=http%3A%2F%2Fkschroeder.pip.verisignlabs.com%2F&openid.claimed_id=http%3A%2F%2Fkschroeder.pip.verisignlabs.com%2F&openid.assoc_handle=c1b035a0-dbd5-11dc-83c8-51f194f14af5&openid.return_to=http%3A%2F%2Ftest.corp.mirageworks.com%2F&openid.realm=http%3A\n\nAs you can see, the realm has been chopped off.   The URL I receive back is\n\nhttp:\/\/test.corp.mirageworks.com\/?openid.ns=http:\/\/openid.net\/signon\/2.0&openid.mode=error&openid.error=BAD_REQUEST\n\nThis is using the most up-to-date revision from http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/svn\/framework\/trunk (8026).  Or is the anonymous SVN at http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/svn\/framework\/trunk not current?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kschroeder",
